post_text:
IXL SUMMER CHALLENGE STARTS MAY 15TH!

Keep doing IXL over the summer and earn a trip to the Movie Theatre in Viborg, SD. Challenge starts May 15, 2020! Each student that completes or gets to 100 on at least 30 grade level or higher skills during the summer will get to join us for an afternoon field trip to the theatre. This means you must master the skill and earn a medal in it.

Once a student meets their 30 skills this achievement will appear in the Freeman Courier and on the Menno School Facebook page.

To check how many skills your child has achieved select the Analytics Tab and then the Progress Tab. Change the skill grades to the student‚Äôs 2019-2020 grade level and higher. Also, change the date range from May 15th to the current date. The only skills that are counted are the ones that reach 100 in their grade level or higher.

Also, remember to have your child continue reading over the summer to help retain skills learned during the school year!

The IXL Challenge is for students that were in PreK through 7th grade this year!

post_text:
The Menno Community Wellness Center has reopened. The old gym has also been made available to wellness members again. The Community Library will be open on Thursday evening during regular hours.

The Wellness Committee will be posting some regulations to follow while using the facilities and equipment. There will be a paper towel dispenser as well as bottles of cleaner to clean equipment before and after you use it.

Additionally, the Menno School Board would like you to know the following: Students may come to the gym and play basketball but will need to bring their own ball. If they play a pickup game, it will be their responsibility for that decision. People can come in and walk in the gym. Coaches can also schedule camps and there can be open gym time. The Board asks that parents make the decision on whether or not their children participate based on the own level of comfort.
5

post_text:
Some people have reported buffering issues while watching our games. Tech support has been contacted. Since some people have been able to watch with no buffering issues they suggest the following:

If you're watching from a computer:
1. Clear your browser's cache and cookies. You may need to search your browser's help section to find instructions.
2. Check your internet connection. You will need to have a connection speed of at least 2 Mbps to stream video.
3. Restart your device. Restart your computer, then check to see if it works as expected.
4. Check for updates. Make sure that your computer has the latest software version.

If you're watching from an iPhone, iPad, Android, Smart TV, etc.:
1. Force quit the app. Close the app and open it again.
2. Restart your device. Restart your device, then open the app to see if it works as expected.
3. Check for updates. Make sure that your device has the latest software version. Then check for app updates.
4. Remove and reinstall the app.

post_text: The 4th Grade class had a special guest today. Michael Fitzmaurice, a Vietnam Veteran and a Congressional Medal of Honor Recipient, shared his story with the class. He also gifted the library with a Medal of Honor book and each student received a special coin. Thank you Mr. Fitzmaurice!

post_text: The FFA Parli Pro team was at the 92nd National FFA Convention where they competed as the South Dakota team. They made it through the first round to the semi-finals where they placed 3rd in their room. This places them 5th or 6th in the nation as there were two rooms with the top 2 teams going on to the finals. This, in itself, is a great accomplishment. However, they all received scores of 80% or better on a written exam, given as part of the competition, which makes them all registered parliamentarians. Great job ladies and gentlemen and congratulations!
text: The FFA Parli Pro team was at the 92nd National FFA Convention where they competed as the South Dakota team. They made it through the first round to the semi-finals where they placed 3rd in their room. This places them 5th or 6th in the nation as there were two rooms with the top 2 teams going on to the finals. This, in itself, is a great accomplishment. However, they all received scores of 80% or better on a written exam, given as part of the competition, which makes them all registered parliamentarians. Great job ladies and gentlemen and congratulations!

post_text: News from the National FFA Convention: The Parliamentary Procedure team have progressed past the 1st round and is one of 16 teams in the semi-final round this morning. post_text:
The 8th Grade class at Menno have organized a variety show as a community service project. The evening of music and comedy will be this Saturday, October 12, at 7:30 pm in the Menno City/School Gym. Admission will be a free will donation. Participants include students, teachers and Menno-Olivet Care Center staff. 100% of the proceeds will be donated to the Menno-Olivet Care Center in order to help pay for a major repair bill for the stand-by generator. An anonymous donor will match up to $1000 toward this fundraiser. Ice cream sundaes and coffee will be served after the show.

This is the 4th year that Mrs. Stoebner's 8th Grade Social Studies class has organized a variety show as a community service project.
